episodes.description: The BAU is in for a ghost of a time when the team investigates a series of ritualistic murders in Oregon.

episodes.title: The Company
episodes.description: When his missing cousin reappears, Morgan is forced to confront a lie he told to protect his family and makes the BAU team reopen the file on her disappearance.

episodes.title: Divining Rod
episodes.description: When a serial murderer is executed, a copycat emerges in Oklahoma, and the BAU team must act swiftly.

episodes.title: Profiling 101
episodes.description: Rossi and the team teach college students about the science of criminal profiling, as they look back on a serial killing case that spanned nearly 20 years.

episodes.title: Hit
episodes.description: The BAU goes up against a gang of bank robbing serial killers, and the stakes rise when one of their own becomes a hostage, on the first part of the two-hour seventh season finale.

episodes.title: Run
episodes.description: The BAU continues to negotiate with the serial killing bank robbers, one of the team gets married and Prentiss ponders her future, on the conclusion of the two-hour seventh season finale.

episodes.title: The Silencer
episodes.description: The team tracks an escaped Texas inmate whose victims bear his unique trademark: Their mouths are sewn shut.

episodes.title: The Pact
episodes.description: When the bodies of two ostensibly unrelated victims are discovered, the team suspects that two killers worked together to carry out the murders.

episodes.title: Through the Looking Glass
episodes.description: The team races against time to find a connection between two Kansas families -- one murdered and the other abducted.

episodes.title: God Complex
episodes.description: When a legless body is discovered in the New Mexico desert, the team is brought in to pursue a surgeon who's performing needless amputations.

episodes.title: The Good Earth
episodes.description: When four men disappear in rural Oregon, the team attempts to track them down by finding a common link among them.

episodes.title: The Apprenticeship
episodes.description: When hookers in Miami are murdered in a style similar to a rash of animal slayings, the team must work fast to find the increasingly confident killer.

episodes.title: The Fallen
episodes.description: The team travels to Santa Monica, Calif., when the burned bodies of homeless people turn up near the city's famous pier.

episodes.title: The Wheels on the Bus..
episodes.description: The team goes in search of a school bus full of students that has vanished near Washington, D.C.

episodes.title: Magnificent Light
episodes.description: When a follower of a well-known motivational speaker is murdered in Seattle, the team suspects the orator -- until he vanishes.

episodes.title: The Lesson
episodes.description: A number of male bodies disposed of in bizarre, ritualistic ways sends the team to Winslow, Ariz., in search of the killer.

episodes.title: Perennials
episodes.description: The team travels south to investigate a suspect whose signature is identical to that of a serial killer whose crimes were committed 30 years earlier.

episodes.title: Zugzwang
episodes.description: When Reid learns that his girlfriend has been abducted by her stalker, he and the team band together to save her before it's too late.

episodes.title: Magnum Opus
episodes.description: While Reid copes with a personal loss, the rest of the team goes to San Francisco to investigate a string of murders in the Mission District.

episodes.title: All That Remains
episodes.description: The team heads to Maryland to profile an author whose wife mysteriously disappeared a year ago -- and whose daughters have just vanished.

episodes.title: Broken
episodes.description: The team investigates when murder victims in Austin, Texas, are found with their watches set incorrectly -- a clue that may link the crimes.

episodes.title: Carbon Copy
episodes.description: The team gets a break in their pursuit of the Replicator -- the BAU's stalker -- when murder victims turn up in Philadelphia.

episodes.title: The Gathering
episodes.description: In St. Paul, Minn., the team investigates the murders of people who were documenting their personal lives and desires on blogs and social media.

episodes.title: Restoration
episodes.description: While on the trail of a killer in Chicago, Morgan comes to believe that the suspect may be linked to the person who molested him as a child.

episodes.title: Pay It Forward
episodes.description: When the opening of a time capsule results in a grisly discovery, the team looks into a potential link to a police officer's death.

episodes.title: Alchemy
episodes.description: The ritualistic murder and dismemberment of two young males sends the team to Rapid City, S.D., to investigate.

episodes.title: Nanny Dearest
episodes.description: In Los Angeles, the team profiles a suspect who abducts nannies and the children in their care on the same date every year.
The team heads to Detroit to probe a pair of murders in which the victims ended up in the trunks of their vehicles.

episodes.title: Brothers Hotchner
episodes.description: When the team probes a series of deaths tied to apparent ecstasy overdoses, Hotch learns that his estranged brother may be involved.

episodes.title: The Replicator
episodes.description: When the Replicator targets a team member as his next victim, the unit must thwart the cunning killer before he can carry out his end game.

episodes.title: The Inspiration: Part 1
episodes.description: The BAU searches for a serial killer in Glendale, Arizona, and the team believes that Hotch is being groomed to replace the late Erin Strauss.

episodes.title: The Inspiration: Part 2
episodes.description: As the BAU close in on the culprit in ritualistic murders in Arizona, they encounter their suspect's mother, who is obviously keeping secrets.

episodes.title: Final Shot
episodes.description: Sniper attacks in Dallas lead the BAU to consider that the incident is motivated by the approaching anniversary of the Kennedy assassination.

episodes.title: To Bear Witness
episodes.description: Mateo Cruz is named section chief over the BAU as the team hunts for a sadistic perp in Baltimore who renders his victims unable to communicate.

episodes.title: Route 66
episodes.description: As a critically wounded Hotch hallucinates moments from his past, the BAU question a man whose estranged teenage daughter has disappeared.

episodes.title: In the Blood
episodes.description: Clues in a series of ritualistic murders in Utah remind the BAU of the Salem witch trials, and Garcia hosts a Day of the Dead party.

episodes.title: Gatekeeper
episodes.description: The BAU searches for a common trait among Boston strangling victims, and Rossi mourns the impending closure of his favorite bar.

episodes.title: The Return
episodes.description: The BAU thinks that missing Chicago teens may be behind a killing spree; Morgan has a hard time accepting his girlfriend's devotion to her work.

episodes.title: Strange Fruit
episodes.description: Shameful family secrets come to light when human remains turn up in the backyard of a home in Virginia.

episodes.title: The Caller
episodes.description: When a young boy disappears from his St. Louis home, the BAU finds connections to a cold case from years earlier.

episodes.title: Bully
episodes.description: A BAU investigation into a string of murders in Kansas City reunites Blake with her estranged father, a retired cop, and brother, a detective.

episodes.title: The Black Queen
episodes.description: Garcia reconnects with an old flame and fellow hacker in hopes of getting help with a BAU murder investigation in San Jose.

episodes.title: The Road Home
episodes.description: Rossi leaves for Los Angeles to search for his former Marine sergeant, who's vanished, while the rest of the BAU searches for a killer in Cleveland.
When JJ is kidnapped, the BAU calls in Prentiss to assist and searches for leads in her missions for the state department.

episodes.title: Mr. and Mrs. Anderson
episodes.description: The BAU realizes that they're actually looking for two culprits in a string of murders in Pittsburgh; Garcia and Morgan make Valentine's Day plans.

episodes.title: Gabby
episodes.description: The BAU reveals some shocking family secrets while investigating the disappearance of a four-year-old girl from a relative's home in Mississippi.

episodes.title: Persuasion
episodes.description: The BAU investigates when a series of bodies turn up in the middle of the Las Vegas desert -- all victims of drowning.

episodes.title: Rabid
episodes.description: Bodies covered with bite marks -- both animal and human -- turn up in a shallow grave outside Milwaukee; Garcia and Reid prepare for a fitness exam.

episodes.title: The Edge of Winter
episodes.description: The BAU is closing an investigation into a stabbing spree in upstate New York when the lone survivor offers information that changes everything.

episodes.title: Blood Relations
episodes.description: The BAU discovers a long-standing feud between a pair of rural clans when two bodies are found in the backwoods of West Virginia.

episodes.title: What Happens in Mecklinburg
episodes.description: The BAU looks for a common element in a series of abductions in Memphis; Savannah confronts Morgan about being gone all the time.

episodes.title: Fatal
episodes.description: A killer with a penchant for ancient Greek philosophy brings the BAU to Long Beach, California, and Hotch prepares for Jack's third grade Career Day.

episodes.title: Angels
episodes.description: The BAU members are caught in the crossfire while investigating the religiously motivated murders of several prostitutes in Texas.

episodes.title: Demons
episodes.description: As they dig deeper into the Texas prostitute murders, the BAU discovers that the killer has a greater -- and much deadlier -- ambition.

episodes.title: X
episodes.description: An undercover agent from the sex crimes unit joins the team in search of a killer who's littering the California desert with dismembered torsos.

episodes.title: Burn
episodes.description: In Seattle, the team hunts down a bizarre killer who carves roman numerals into his victims' mouths; Garcia attends an execution.

episodes.title: A Thousand Suns
episodes.description: When a commercial jet full of passengers crashes in a Colorado field, the team discovers that the plane was brought down by remote control.

episodes.title: The Itch
episodes.description: The team probes the death of an investigative journalist who walked into oncoming traffic and had mysterious scars and scratches on his body.

episodes.title: Boxed In
episodes.description: The team goes to San Diego to investigate the sudden reappearance of a boy who vanished on Halloween one year earlier and was held captive in a box.

episodes.title: If the Shoe Fits
episodes.description: The team goes to Montana, where three young men are found dead with cell phones stuffed in their mouths with the alarms set to go off at midnight.

episodes.title: Hashtag
episodes.description: The team looks into the murder of a teen whose corpse appears in a selfie on social media sites; Morgan struggles to find private time with Savannah.

episodes.title: The Boys of Sudworth Place
episodes.description: When a defense attorney known for working with troubled youth is abducted, the team wonders if the disappearance is linked to one of his cases.

episodes.title: Fate
episodes.description: The team is called to Virginia, where victims are being brutally stabbed, then neatly displayed in fresh clothes; Rossi receives a surprising visitor.

episodes.title: Amelia Porter
episodes.description: In Salt Lake City, the team investigates a triple homicide that puts them on the trail of a fugitive who disappeared after committing a grisly crime.

episodes.title: The Forever People
episodes.description: In Boulder City, Nevada, the team looks for a serial killer amidst a cult that freezes members as part of their induction ritual.

episodes.title: Anonymous
episodes.description: When a string of seemingly unrelated murders occurs in Tallahassee, the team learns the victims were all organ donors; Rossi loses a close friend.

episodes.title: Nelson's Sparrow
episodes.description: A case hits home for Rossi when a colleague from his past is found murdered, setting him on the trail of a bird-obsessed serial killer.

episodes.title: Hero Worship
episodes.description: When an Indianapolis coffee shop explodes and the media rallies around a local hero, the team's seemingly open-and-shut case could go up in smoke.

episodes.title: Scream
episodes.description: The team is called in to investigate the deaths of two California women found in dumpsters with their bodies beaten and throats slashed.

episodes.title: Lockdown
episodes.description: The warden of a maximum security prison calls on the team when two guards are murdered, but more danger looms when the trouble escalates into a riot.

episodes.title: Breath Play
episodes.description: In Wisconsin, the team hunts for a serial killer whose victims are obsessed with a best-selling erotic novel; Kate suspects her niece has a secret.

episodes.title: Rock Creek Park
episodes.description: When the wife of a junior congressman is abducted, the unit discovers that the motives behind the crime are not what the FBI suspects.

episodes.title: Beyond Borders
episodes.description: When a family on vacation in the Caribbean is abducted, the team is called upon to assist Special Agent Jack Garrett and his team in Barbados.

episodes.title: A Place at the Table
episodes.description: The team investigates the murder of a family found dead at their dining room table; Hotch helps Jessica keep Roy out of a nursing home.

episodes.title: Mr. Scratch
episodes.description: The unit searches for a criminal who puts his victims into a violent hallucinogenic state, causing them to kill their loved ones.

episodes.title: Protection
episodes.description: The team takes the case of a delusional killer who believes he is punishing criminals; Kate's niece sneaks out at night with a stranger.

episodes.title: The Hunt
episodes.description: When Kate's niece and her friend are kidnapped, the team rushes to find them before they become victims of traffickers.

episodes.title: The Job
episodes.description: As the BAU searches for a serial killer who paints his victims' faces, prospective new team member Tara Lewis gets a chance to show off her skills.

episodes.title: The Witness
episodes.description: A poison gas attack on a commuter bus brings the team to L.A., where they zero in on a businessman who was late to work and is acting strangely.

episodes.title: 'Til Death Do Us Part
episodes.description: The murder of two brides-to-be in Savannah, Georgia, leaves the team looking for a jilted lover. But a third body forces them to rethink the profile.

episodes.title: Outlaw
episodes.description: When three teens are found slain in a New Mexico restaurant, the team sees uncanny similarities to a cold case from six years ago.

episodes.title: The Night Watch
episodes.description: An elaborate murder scene triggers a search for a street artist whose identity is a well-kept secret. Work takes a toll on Lewis's home life.

episodes.title: Pariahville
episodes.description: A killing in a town populated by sex offenders presents a daunting challenge for the team. Meanwhile, Lewis receives a tempting job offer.

episodes.title: Target Rich
episodes.description: As the team celebrates JJ's return, Rossi's daughter begs for help finding a missing college student. An interview with Montolo takes a dramatic turn.

episodes.title: Awake
episodes.description: The BAU races to track down a man who's abducting and torturing victims along a Phoenix highway. A threat forces Garcia to bunk down at the office.

episodes.title: Internal Affairs
episodes.description: After an attack on undercover DEA agents in Texas, the NSA calls in Hotch's team to investigate an online drug cartel and root out an agency mole.

episodes.title: Future Perfect
episodes.description: Two bodies found with strange markings in Florida spur a hunt for a suspect with medical knowledge and a morbid fixation.

episodes.title: Entropy
episodes.description: As the team closes in on the network of hitmen threatening Garcia, Reid becomes locked in a high-stakes showdown with a woman known as "Miss .45."

episodes.title: Drive
episodes.description: The BAU traces a series of headless bodies in Boston to a ride-sharing service. But there's something more that the victims have in common.

episodes.title: The Bond
episodes.description: While the team struggles to connect the dots between several truck stop killings, a troubled man reconnects with his long-lost biological mother.

episodes.title: Hostage
episodes.description: After an 18-year-old escapes from a basement where she's been held captive for years, the race is on to find her tormentor and his other victims.

episodes.title: A Badge and a Gun
episodes.description: Adding up clues from several suffocations in L.A., the team begins to fear the killer is a rogue FBI agent. A text from Savannah puts Morgan on edge.

episodes.title: Derek
episodes.description: To survive an agonizing ordeal, Morgan slips into a trance, where he connects with his late father and realizes what Savannah wanted to tell him.

episodes.title: The Sandman
episodes.description: The BAU welcomes Morgan back after a six-month leave, but the celebration is cut short by news of a ritualistic family murder in Kansas.

episodes.title: A Beautiful Disaster
episodes.description: On a quest to find out who targeted Morgan and Savannah, the team uncovers links to a past case. A note from the sniper leads to a harrowing showdown.

episodes.title: Tribute
episodes.description: Emily Prentiss reunites with the BAU to track down a murderer who's mimicking crimes by famous serial killers like Jack the Ripper and Son of Sam.

episodes.title: Inner Beauty
episodes.description: The team tries to figure out what drives a killer to disfigure his female victims' faces. Rossi reconnects with someone from his past.

episodes.title: Devil's Backbone
episodes.description: A notorious female serial killer draws the members of the BAU into a twisted mind game when they ask her for help finding two missing boys.

episodes.title: The Storm
episodes.description: When Hotch is arrested in a SWAT raid, the team scrambles to clear his name, but they soon realize it's part of a larger plot that's unfolding fast.

episodes.title: The Crimson King
episodes.description: A new agent, Luke Alvez, joins the team to help them catch the Crimson King, one of the escaped killers from last season.

episodes.title: Sick Day
episodes.description: Fresh from the tragic aftermath of a child abduction case, a vulnerable JJ returns home to find that her youngest child is sick.

episodes.title: Taboo
episodes.description: The gruesome murder of three single mothers leads to an investigation of what they had in common and why they were killed.

episodes.title: Keeper
episodes.description: The body parts of several people who had gone missing over a period of six months are discovered in a homeless man's shopping cart.

episodes.title: The Anti-Terrorism Squad
episodes.description: A 17-year-old girl returns home, well past her curfew, to run into the dead bodies of her family members, who have been shot execution-style.

episodes.title: Elliott's Pond
episodes.description: The team is called in to investigate after three children go missing in the same area where two children disappeared 30 years ago.

episodes.title: Mirror Image
episodes.description: The team launches an investigation into the sudden arrival of a mysterious man claiming to be Tara's younger brother, Gabriel.

episodes.title: Scarecrow
episodes.description: The team heads to Yakima, Washington, after a local girl goes missing and the remains of several people are found along a creek bed.

episodes.title: Profiling 202
episodes.description: A familiar voice from the past calls Rossi on his birthday to inform him that he has abducted a woman, and he has more information to share.

episodes.title: Seek & Destroy
episodes.description: The team investigates a series of brutal, destructive home invasions that end in murder in upscale San Diego neighborhoods.

episodes.title: Surface Tension
episodes.description: While dissecting a corpse in an anatomy class, a teacher and her students discover a strange mark that was found on another dead body.

episodes.title: A Good Husband
episodes.description: The discoveries of two male torsos within close proximity of each other in Palm Springs appear to point to a single killer.

episodes.title: Spencer
episodes.description: Spencer is arrested near the U.S.-Mexico border, after a stash of heroin is discovered in the trunk of the vehicle that he's driving.

episodes.title: Collision Course
episodes.description: Two pedestrians are run down on the same road by two similar vehicles, leading the team to wonder if the incidents point to a pattern.

episodes.title: Alpha Male
episodes.description: With Spencer's incarceration at the back of their minds, the BAU heads to Philadelphia to investigate a series of acid attacks.

episodes.title: Assistance is Futile
episodes.description: A number of corpses are found in New York City, victims of a serial killer with an evident fondness for breaking bones.

episodes.title: In the Dark
episodes.description: A series of home invasion stabbings and shootings of hunters in Vermont have the team wondering if they are dealing with two killers.

episodes.title: Hell's Kitchen
episodes.description: A girl's disappearance in New York City just before her 16th birthday appears to have similarities to two previous abduction killings.

episodes.title: True North
episodes.description: The dead bodies of three victims are discovered tied to stakes in the Arizona desert, and in varying stages of decomposition.

episodes.title: Unforgettable
episodes.description: Stephen's friend from the BAP is hospitalized following what looks like a heart attack but it turns out to be something more.

episodes.title: Green Light
episodes.description: The victim of one of the team's former cases turns up, posing as a nurse to Spencer's mother, shortly before the latter disappears.

episodes.title: Red Light
episodes.description: Reid finds himself returning to prison for an unusual tête-à-tête with the accomplice of the girl who abducted his mother.

episodes.title: Space Pilot 3000
episodes.description: A pizza delivery boy named Fry awakens from a state of suspended animation and finds himself in a futuristic world populated by aliens, robots and spaceships.

episodes.title: The Series Has Landed
episodes.description: Fry eagerly anticipates his first visit to the moon...only to realize that it is home to a cheesy amusement park.

episodes.title: I, Roommate
episodes.description: Fry and Bender become a futuristic odd couple when they attempt to share an apartment.

episodes.title: Love's Labours Lost In Space
episodes.description: Leela finds herself the object of a starship captain's amorous advances.

episodes.title: Fear of a Bot Planet
episodes.description: Fry and Lela find themselves trapped on a planet ruled by human-hating robots.

episodes.title: A Fishful of Dollars
episodes.description: Fry discovers that a small amount of money left in his old bank account has accumulated into a fortune. But his nostalgia for all things 20th century puts him at odds with an evil oil tycoon.

episodes.title: My Three Suns
episodes.description: The crew visits a planet inhabited by liquid aliens. Fry, after delivering a package under the scorching heat of the planet's three suns, finds a bottle of cool blue liquid to quench his thirst. But when that liquid turns out to be the civilization's ruler, Fry finds he has become the new leader. Initially drunk with power, he soon discovers his life is in danger and must turn to his friends to help him dry out.

episodes.title: A Big Piece of Garbage
episodes.description: A gigantic ball of garbage carelessly launched off Earth in the 21st century returns on a collision course for New New York City and Fry and the crew set out on a mission to destroy it.

episodes.title: Hell Is Other Robots
episodes.description: Bender seeks religion after becoming addicted to electricity.

episodes.title: A Flight to Remember
episodes.description: Ep10 - As the Planet Express team vacations aboard the starship Titanic, the vessel falls victim to the gravitational pull of a black hole.

episodes.title: Mars University
episodes.description: Fry enrolls in Mars University, only to discover that his dorm roommate is a super intelligent monkey; Bender teaches a fraternity of robots how to be cool.

episodes.title: When Aliens Attack
episodes.description: Fry and his friends fight off an alien invasion of Earth by recreating a television drama from the 20th century featuring a sexily-attired single female lawyer.

episodes.title: Fry and the Slurm Factory
episodes.description: Fry wins a contest that takes the crew on a tour of the Slurm factory...and exposes its terrible secret.

episodes.title: I Second That Emotion
episodes.description: After Bender flushes Nibbler down a toilet, Fry, Leela and Bender journey through a sewer system inhabited by mutants.

episodes.title: Brannigan, Begin Again
episodes.description: After being court-martialed Zap Brannigan joins the Planet Express team...only to inspire Fry and Bender to mutiny against Leela.

episodes.title: A Head in the Polls
episodes.description: When the price of titanium skyrockets, Bender hocks his titanium-rich body to a pawnshop and lives the good life, until Richard Nixon s head uses the robot's torso to stage a political comeback.

episodes.title: Xmas Story
episodes.description: Fry and Leela find themselves targeted by a murderous robotic Santa Claus; Bender volunteers at a shelter for homeless robots.

episodes.title: Why Must I Be a Crustacean in Love
episodes.description: When Zoidberg runs amok during mating season, Fry sets out to teach him how to woo a mate.

episodes.title: Put Your Head on My Shoulders
episodes.description: Valentine's Day turns into a nightmare for Fry after his head is surgically attached to Amy's body.

episodes.title: The Lesser of Two Evils
episodes.description: Fry fears the worst when Bender's exact duplicate joins the crew on a mission to deliver a valuable atomic tiara to The Miss Universe pageant.

episodes.title: Raging Bender
episodes.description: Bender's popularity soars when he becomes a successful pro-wrestler, but when he is instructed to lose a fight, Leela steps into help him defeat an opponent trained by her old master.

episodes.title: A Bicyclops Built for Two
episodes.description: Leela finally encounters another member of her race, a handsome male. But when he turns out to be a jerk, she fears that leaving him will mean her species' extinction.

episodes.title: How Hermes Requisitioned His Groove Back
episodes.description: Hermes grows despondent when he misses an opportunity for a promotion; a female bureaucrat is turned-on by Fry's sloppiness.

episodes.title: A Clone of My Own
episodes.description: The Professor chooses his clone, Cubert, as the successor to his research...only to realize that Cubert has dreams of his own.

episodes.title: The Deep South
episodes.description: Deep beneath the ocean, the crew discovers the lost city of Atlantis where Fry falls hopelessly in love with mermaid.

episodes.title: Bender Gets Made
episodes.description: After joining the robot Mafia, Bender finds himself involved in scheme to loot the Planet Express spaceship of its cargo and destroy the crew.

episodes.title: The Problem With Popplers
episodes.description: Powerful alien beings threaten to devour of all mankind after the Planet Express crew inadvertently introduces earthlings to the aliens' tasty offspring.

episodes.title: Mother's Day
episodes.description: On Mother's Day, Mom unleashes hoard of rampaging robots to destroy the Earth-and only the Professor can stop them.

episodes.title: Anthology of Interest I
episodes.description: The Professor's "What-If" machine simulates Bender, Leela and Fry's wishes: Bender turns into a giant robot; Leela impulsively murders her friends; Vice President Al Gore, Stephen Hawking, Gary Gygax, and Nichelle Nichols come to the rescue when Fry inadvertently opens a rip in the space-time continuum.

episodes.title: The Honking
episodes.description: When Bender inherits a castle from his deceased uncle, he finds himself being pursued by a terrifying, driverless car.

episodes.title: War is the H-Word
episodes.description: Fry and Bender face off against an army of aliens on a far-off planet after they join the army to qualify for military discounts.

episodes.title: The Cryonic Woman
episodes.description: A woman from Fry's past unthaws in the year 3000, but when she feels out of place, she and Fry journey a thousand years into the future.

episodes.title: Parasites Lost
episodes.description: A miniature version of the Planet Express crew attempts to rid Fry's body of parasitic worms; meanwhile, Leela finds Fry's new personality irresistible.

episodes.title: Amazon Women in the Mood
episodes.description: Fry and the others find themselves trapped on a planet of Amazonian women ruled by a man-hating computer.

episodes.title: Bendless Love
episodes.description: Bender finds true romance with a coworker after crossing a picket line, but jealousy over his love's ex-boyfriend threatens to destroy everything.

episodes.title: The Day the Earth Stood Stupid
episodes.description: Only Fry can save Earth when evil brains from another world plot to make everyone stupid.

episodes.title: That's Lobstertainment!
episodes.description: Dr. Zoidberg promises his uncle-washed-up comedian Harold Zoid-that he will invest a million dollars in his Hollywood movie.

episodes.title: The Birdbot of Ice-Catraz
episodes.description: Leela fights to save the lives of penguins after the Planet Express ship is involved in an oil spill on Pluto.

episodes.title: The Luck of the Fryrish
episodes.description: Fry searches the ancient ruins of Old New York for his beloved lucky clover...only to conclude that his older brother stole not only the clover-but his life.

episodes.title: The Cyber House Rules
episodes.description: Tired of feeling like an outcast, Leela has a second eye grafted onto her face; Bender adopts twelve children after learning about the government's seemingly lucrative stipend.

episodes.title: Insane in the Mainframe
episodes.description: Fry and Bender become inadvertent participants in a bank robbery and are sentenced to a robot insane asylum where Fry comes to believe that he is indeed a robot.

episodes.title: Bendin' in the Wind
episodes.description: Bender is broken in a freak accident, but meets Beck who launches him on a singing career that turns him into a hero for other broken robots.

episodes.title: Time Keeps on Slipping
episodes.description: While creating a team of mutants to play the Harlem Globetrotters, the Professor accidentally causes a disruption in time that threatens the existence of the universe.

episodes.title: I Dated a Robot
episodes.description: Fry realizes a lifelong dream by dating a Lucy Liu robot.

episodes.title: Roswell That Ends Well
episodes.description: When the Planet Express ship travels through time to Roswell, New Mexico in 1947, Fry becomes his own progeny.

episodes.title: A Tale of Two Santas
episodes.description: As Christmas approaches...Bender faces execution when he fills in for the murderous Santa robot.

episodes.title: Anthology of Interest II
episodes.description: The What-If Machine tells Bender what it would be like if he were human, Fry what it would be like if life were like a video game, and Leela what it would be like if she found her true home.

episodes.title: Love & Rocket
episodes.description: As Valentine's Day approaches...Bender's romance with the Planet Express Ship puts the crew in jeopardy.

episodes.title: Leela's Homeworld

episodes.title: Where the Buggalo Roam
episodes.description: Although Kif, Amy's boyfriend, retrieves her parents' buggalo herd and rescues Amy when she is kidnapped, they still refuse to accept him.

episodes.description: Bender's longing to be remembered motivates him to become a tyrannical Pharaoh on Osiris 4.

episodes.title: Godfellas
episodes.description: Bender accidentally gets shot out into the heavens and becomes god to a race of tiny aliens only to fail in that position and meet the Real Thing.

episodes.description: A cryogenically frozen 1980's guy is thawed, becomes the CEO of the failing Planet Express company, and threatens to have it acquired and gutted by it's largest competitor.

episodes.description: The Planet Express crew finds itself pitted against the cast of the original Star Trek when an energy creature seeks to determine who is more worthy of his fanatical devotion.

episodes.title: Crimes of the Hot
episodes.description: When the Earth is jeopardized by global warming, the crew attends a conference in Kyoto hosted by Al Gore's head. Richard Nixon's head attempts to rid the planet of robots -including Bender.

episodes.title: Jurassic Bark
episodes.description: Bender grows jealous when Fry attempts to clone his beloved fossilized dog.

episodes.description: Hermes' and the Professor's sons try to outdo them in the business world but need their dads' help when success overwhelms them; Bender becomes a brewmiester.

episodes.title: A Taste of Freedom
episodes.description: In celebration of Freedom Day, Dr. Zoidberg eats the Earth flag, for which he is sentenced to death. In retaliation, the Decapodians enslave the entire world.

episodes.title: Kif Gets Knocked Up a Notch
episodes.description: When Kif gets pregnant,Amy questions her readiness to become a parent.

episodes.title: Less Than Hero
episodes.description: When Fry and Leela discover a mysterious cream that gives them unusual powers, they form a Superhero team along with Bender.

episodes.title: Teenage Mutant Leela's Hurdles
episodes.description: The Planet Express crew is exposed to a substance that causes everyone to revert to teenagers...and the Professor's attempt to correct the problem only makes thing worse.

episodes.description: Nibbler enlists Fry in a mission to blow up evil brains bent on destroying the universe; Fry time travels into the past to prevent himself from being cryogenically frozen.

episodes.title: The Sting
episodes.description: A killer bee sting sends Leela on a long, strange trip.

episodes.title: The Farnsworth Parabox
episodes.description: The Planet Express crew goes to a parallel universe made accessible by Professor Farnsworth's latest experiment.

episodes.description: When each Earthican receives a three hundred-dollar government refund, the Planet Express crew members pursue their respective dreams and desires.

episodes.description: S5, E12 When Fry succeeds in retrieving his nose, which was taken by aliens, a more precious appendage of his is placed in peril.

episodes.title: Beast With a Billion Backs - Part 1
episodes.description: Fry and the crew discover a giant hole in the universe and a seductive one-eyed tentacular alien on the other side.

episodes.title: The Beast with a Billion Backs - Part 2
episodes.description: Zap leads a military strike on the anomaly; a heartbroken Fry decides to leave the Universe; and Bender's obsession with the League of Robots bears fruit.

episodes.title: The Beast with a Billion Backs - Part 3
episodes.description: A tentacle creature from the Universe beyond the anomaly takes over our Universe; Leela, Amy, and Zap become the only resistance; and Bender becomes disillusioned with the League of Robots.

episodes.title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 3
episodes.description: Zapp, Kiff, and Bender try to capture the feministas. Fry secretly goes undercover working for Wong and learns about the Dark Ones and the Encyclopods.

episodes.title: Into the Wild Green Yonder - Part 4
episodes.description: Leela, Amy, and the Feministas are charged and stand trial for murder, mayhem, vandalism, kidnapping and resisting arrest.

episodes.description: Bender joins the paparazzi and attempts to photograph a famous actor whose face has never been seen.

episodes.description: Dr. Zoidberg meets the love of his life while Bender squares off in a deadly tap dancing competition.

episodes.title: Take Your Little Gun and Get Out of My Trailer Park
episodes.description: After an 18-month jail sentence, Ricky and Julian head home to get their lives back together but a bully has taken control of the park.

episodes.description: Julian decides to depart Sunnyvale Trailer Park and go to community college to finally do something productive in his life.

episodes.description: Ricky and Bubbles agree to star in J-Roc's porno film but Ricky loses his nerve, forcing Bubbles to stand in for him on a particularly steamy scene.

episodes.description: Ricky lets a dog devour a tray of hash brownies and takes the dog to the local veterinarian. He must then run errands for the vet to pay for it.

episodes.description: Julian convinces Ricky that it's time to marry Lucy. Reluctant at first, Ricky changes his mind when Julian suggests that people will assume he's gay.

episodes.description: Lucy asks Julian to plan the wedding since she thinks Ricky is not up to it, but his plans ruin the wedding when the cops show up.

episodes.title: Jim Lahey Is a Drunk Bastard
episodes.description: Julian and Ricky have to make sure that Jim Lahey wins the election for trailer park supervisor over their archrival Sam Losco, who is also running.

episodes.title: I've Met Cats and Dogs Smarter than Trevor and Cory
episodes.description: Needing extra cash to expand their dope operation without raising Lahey's suspicions, Julian and Ricky open a disco bar in J-Roc's trailer.

episodes.title: A Dope Trailer Is No Place for a Kitty
episodes.description: When their dope plants become infested with insects, Ricky and Julian quarantine the surviving crop in Bubbles's shed, leading to a fiery conclusion.

episodes.title: The Bible Pimp
episodes.description: A couple pretending to be a preacher and his daughter selling Bibles comes to the park, hoping to make off with lots of cash.

episodes.title: Never Trust a Man with No Shirt On
episodes.description: Randy joins Julian and Ricky in their life of crime. However, when Randy is caught spying on them, it puts their dope operation in danger.

episodes.title: The Bare Pimp Project
episodes.description: Julian asks J-Roc to make another porno film to make Barb dump Sam, Ricky gets his Grade 10, and Julian successfully sells the hash.

episodes.title: The Kiss of Freedom
episodes.description: After their release from prison, Ricky and Julian are free and rich, thanks to their huge dope sale to the prison guards and inmates.

episodes.title: Temporary Relief Assistant Trailer Park Supervisor
episodes.description: Ricky wins the new position of temporary relief assistant trailer park supervisor after Randy is suspended by Barb Lahey.

episodes.title: If I Can't Smoke and Swear I'm F**ked
episodes.description: Julian reveals a new plan to the boys that involves committing various small crimes so they can't go to jail, and saving the money for a cruise trip.

episodes.description: When ripped off on buying Rush tickets by Lahey and Randy, Ricky "borrows" guitarist Alex Lifeson for tickets. Lifeson's hotel room number is 2112.

episodes.description: Ricky conspires to get rich by using kids to help him steal barbecues, as minors are protected under the Youth Justice Act.

episodes.description: Upon realizing that he has no ticket for the eagerly awaited cruise and being evicted from the trailer park, Ricky is determined to go back to jail.

episodes.description: After eight months behind bars, Julian, Mr. Lahey and Randy are released, only to discover that Ricky is the new supervisor of Sunnyvale Trailer Park.

episodes.description: Broke and tired of Ricky's illegal plans, Julian decides to leave the trailer park to live in his car. Meanwhile, Randy resorts to prostitution.

episodes.description: Ricky and Bubbles mistake Julian for a "Samsquanch" and beat up each other with baseball bats. They also open a massage parlor in the park.

episodes.description: When Ricky plans to have a community day in the park complete with wrestling, Bubbles assumes the identity of a wrestler from "parts unknown."

episodes.title: Conky
episodes.description: When Bubbles has a toothache, he tries everything to get rid of it. Julian tells him that he must go to the hospital.

episodes.title: If You Love Something Set It Free
episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles find a mountain lion in their marijuana field eating their weed. Things get complicated when Bubbles befriends the animal.

episodes.title: Propane, Propane
episodes.description: The boys plan to smuggle the dope and sell it at a Snoop Dogg concert. Lahey asks Barb to marry him again, but Barb declines.

episodes.title: Working Man
episodes.description: The boys hold Rita MacNeil and her entourage hostage and force them to help harvest the dope crop. A hostile standoff ensues.

episodes.title: Give Peace a Chance
episodes.description: After a brief stint in jail, Ricky, Julian and Bubbles return to the trailer park in style, but soon discover that Trevor and Cory lost their money.

episodes.title: The Sh*t Puppets
episodes.description: Cory and Trevor go to work for Julian and help him steal hash from Cyrus, Terry and Dennis, then concoct a plan to hide it until they find a buyer.

episodes.title: The F**kin Way She Goes
episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles hide their hash under Ray's driveway. Ray's addictions worsen. Ricky barbecues for his family, with devastating results.

episodes.title: You Got to Blame the Thing Up Here
episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles help Ray find a new home after his trailer burns down in a fire that Ricky caused. However, it's Bubbles who gets the blame.

episodes.title: Jim Lahey Is a F**kin' Drunk and He Always Will Be
episodes.description: Bubbles pretends to be a spaceman when the boys steal a rocket set. Ray reveals Lahey's secret, and Lahey goes off the deep end.

episodes.title: Don't Cross the Sh*t Line
episodes.description: Ray and Bubbles star in another of J-Roc's adult films, but Lahey and Randy confiscate J-Roc's tape, which has evidence of Ray's disability fraud.

episodes.title: The Winds of Sh*t
episodes.description: Ricky tries to go back to school but ends up working as a janitor selling dope to the students. Lahey has disturbing visions of the future.

episodes.title: Dressed All Over & Zesty Mordant
episodes.description: Julian's biggest moneymaking scheme involves smuggling the hash using the shopping carts at a local mall. Trinity gets charged with underage driving.

episodes.title: I Am the Liquor
episodes.description: Ricky bails Trinity out of jail. Lahey goes on a bender and tricks Cory and Trevor into giving him information. Julian tries to get his trailer back.

episodes.title: Sh*t Blizzard
episodes.description: Cyrus and his gang are bailed out of jail by Randy and immediately go after Ricky, Julian and Bubbles for getting them busted and taking their hash.

episodes.title: Way of the Road
episodes.description: Ray gets booted out of Sunnyvale, Julian sells booze in jail, Randy gets fed up with Lahey's drinking, and Bubbles opens a daycare for cats.

episodes.title: The Cheeseburger Picnic
episodes.description: While Randy organizes a trailer park-wide cheeseburger picnic, Lahey pretends to be drunk in hopes of catching the boys breaking the law.

episodes.title: High Definition Piss Jugs
episodes.description: When a local TV station comes to Sunnyvale, Cory and Trevor try to publicize their business, and Bubbles promotes his Kittyland Love Center.

episodes.title: Where in the F**k Is Oscar Goldman?
episodes.description: Bubbles's kitty daycare gets some actual customers, and Ricky and Julian must track down Trinity's lost chicken to keep her from failing sixth grade.

episodes.title: Halloween 1977
episodes.description: Randy goes nuts with his eviction policy, and Lahey uncovers evidence that the boys were behind the prank that got him fired from the police force.

episodes.title: Gimme My F**king Money or Randy's Dead
episodes.description: Blaming Randy for getting him fired, Sam Losco takes him captive and holds him for ransom. Meanwhile, Bubbles helps Lahey get back his badge.

episodes.description: Ricky and Bubbles try to profit by selling stolen meat from a grocery store. Meanwhile, Lucy is pregnant and more demanding to Ricky.

episodes.description: Officers George Green and Ted Johnston attempt to kill Lahey, Randy and Phil Collins for not filing search warrants against Julian and J-Roc.

episodes.description: At a model train convention hosted by Sebastian Bach, Ray gets busted for soliciting an undercover cop, leaving Bubbles stranded in a phone booth.

episodes.description: Julian comes up with a plan to smuggle dope into Maine by using a model train that Bubbles stole.

episodes.description: The boys head to the woods in search of Jacob and his friends and soon come across Julian's 1987 Monte Carlo in the river.

episodes.description: Randy and Phil Collins are busy with final preparations before the opening of The Dirty Burger, including a bicycle stunt by Randy that goes wrong.

episodes.title: Let the Liquor Do the Thinking
episodes.description: Randy and Lahey get back together with the help of alcohol. Randy tries to break off his engagement with Lucy. Bubbles is having problems.

episodes.title: Going Off the Rails on the Swayzie Train
episodes.description: The Boys proceed with their cross-border shipment plan with Sebastian Bach. But can they trust their crew?

episodes.description: This episode revolves around the conclusion of the boys' plan to smuggle dope to the United States. As usual, the plan doesn't go quite to plan.

episodes.description: The boys each have new moneymaking schemes, Jim Lahey is on the verge of retiring and Randy has a new assistant.

episodes.description: Julian offers to partner with Barb so that she can keep the trailer park, but they need Jim Lahey's cooperation over his deciding one percent share.

episodes.description: When Orangie, Ricky's goldfish, dies after being given too many shooters, Julian and Bubbles try to replace it with another before Ricky finds out.

episodes.description: TV celebrity Steve Rogers rents Julian's bar for his stag party, which gets of out hand and overflows into Bubbles's Shed-and-Breakfast sheds.

episodes.title: Friends with the Benedicts
episodes.description: Bubbles's attempts to clear up a crab infestation in his sheds and on his kitties cause him embarrassment, and he's arrested for indecent exposure.

episodes.description: Sentenced to community service, Bubbles insists that Julian and Ricky help him with a school puppet show. The Green Bastard teaches Ricky a lesson.

episodes.description: When the compressor air conditioner breaks, Bubbles has to turn his sheds into an industrial honey oil manufacturing complex to save Ricky's weed.

episodes.description: While being filmed by George Green, Bubbles gets his oil production going, aiming to make enough money to buy the trailer park for Barb and Julian.

episodes.title: Crawling Through the Sh*tpipe
episodes.description: The boys sell their entire honey oil output to Sebastian Bach, but to seal the deal for the trailer park, Julian has to do something truly terrible.

episodes.title: Why in the F**k Is My Trailer Pink?
episodes.description: Julian and Ricky get out of jail and return to the Sunnyvale Trailer Park, but when they arrive, they find that nothing is as they left it.

episodes.description: Ricky tries to keep his family together despite not being allowed back in the park, while Julian and Bubbles try to get business going again.

episodes.description: Julian hatches a plan to secure a place to live while Ricky and his family struggle with their new life in the barn.

episodes.description: Julian and his crew have a motel auction while Ricky must track down a list full of baby items to keep his family together.

episodes.title: The Motel Can't Live at the Motel
episodes.description: Ricky brings his grandson home to the motel, but it doesn't go as planned, and Julian implements the first stage in his bid to get Sunnyvale back.

episodes.title: Sweet Liquory Load
